Tutorials

Basics

     * [http://pixeljoint.com/forum/forum_posts.asp?TID=11299]Introduction
       to pixel art
     * [http://vanmall.deviantart.com/art/How-to-start-with-pixel-art-1215
       20884]Creating a cube
     * [http://vanmall.deviantart.com/art/How-to-make-round-objects-in-pix
       el-art-347907700]Creating round objects
     * [http://samkeddy.com/pixel-art-outlines/]Outline basics
     * [http://samkeddy.com/pixel-art-outlines-part-2-using-color/]Outline
       colors

Color

     * [https://betterin2d.com/2014/08/02/pixel-art-tutorial-creating-a-co
       lour-palette/]Creating a color palette
     * [https://opengameart.org/content/chapter-5-color-palettes]Color
       palette and HSL

Animation

     * [http://www.manningkrull.com/pixel-art/walking.php]Walking
       animation for low-res sprites
     * [http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/176663/5_tips_for_making_great_
       animations_for_2D_games.php]Tips for animating 2D games

Inspiration

Games

     * [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yoshi%27s_Island]Super Mario World
       2: Yoshi's Island - Play as Yoshi carrying Baby Mario, platforming
       through a dangerous world. The painted feel and soft pastel colors
       create an hearth-warming handmade style that breathes the charm of
       a children's book.
     * [http://www.fezgame.com/]FEZ - Explore a 2D retrofuturistic world
       by rotating in the third dimension. The minimalistic style, bright
       vibrant colors and dynamic lighting bring the 16-bit era into the
       future.
     * [http://www.swordandsworcery.com/]Superbrothers: Sword & Sworcery
       EP - Laid back adventure in a bronze age mountain wilderness.
       Dreamy soft colors in a living world affected by moon phases.
     * [http://yachtclubgames.com/shovel-knight/]Shovel Knight: Treasure
       Trove - Classic action adventure with an 8-bit retro aesthetic,
       taking the looks of a modern NES game.
     * [http://www.heart-machine.com/]Hyper Light Drifter - Top-down
       action in a sci-fi world that radiates light and warmth. Using a
       colorful palette and kaleidoscopic neon yet setting a grim
       ambiance.
     * [http://www.owlboygame.com/]Owlboy - Explore a detailed steampunk
       world in the clouds. With it's range of endearing animations and
       expressions the world and it's characters come to life.
     * [https://stardewvalley.net/]Stardew Valley - Manage a farm from a
       top-down perspective and engage with a charming and cheerful world
       in 16-bit.

Artists

     * [http://probertson.tumblr.com/]Paul Robertson - Australian,
       creating cute, sometimes cosmic and psychedelic, and sometimes
       weird nightmarish pixel art.
     * [http://collet66.blog52.fc2.com/]Syosa - Japanese, girlish style
       using bright and organic color palletes creating cute humans and
       animals.
     * [http://cyangmou.deviantart.com/]Thomas Feichtmeir - Australian,
       dark and mature: fan of knights, dinosaurs, pirates, epic beasts,
       anatomy and history as well as everything twisted and weird.
     * [http://1041uuu.tumblr.com/]Toyoi Yuuta - Australian, capturing
       small animated scenes of everyday life in unsaturated colors.

Tools

     * [http://aseprite.org/]Aseprite - Open source, paid with trial,
       works on Linux, macOS and Windows. Awesome UI with a lot of nifty
       tools to ease pixel art creation.
     * [https://pixenapp.com/]Pixen - Paid, works on macOS and iOS. Superb
       OS integration, create pixel art on a tablet using
       pressure-sensitive drawing.
     * [http://www.cosmigo.com/pixel_animation_software]Pro Motion - Paid
       with trial, works on Windows. Advanced features tailored to
       creating pixel art for games.
     * [https://www.gimp.org/]GIMP - Open source and free, works on Linux,
       macOS and Windows. Not specifically for creating pixel art but is
       more than capable to do so.
     * [http://www.piskelapp.com/]Piskel - Open source and free, works in
       the browser, on Linux, macOS and Windows. Easy to try out in the
       browser saving sprites online.

